WEBVTT

00:01.169 --> 00:03.737
You know the kind of guy
who does nothing
but bad things...

00:03.771 --> 00:06.674
and then wonders why
his life sucks?

00:06.707 --> 00:11.112
Well, that was me.
Every time somethin' good
happened to me,

00:11.145 --> 00:13.247
somethin' bad
was always waitin'
around the corner.

00:15.449 --> 00:17.051
Karma.

00:17.085 --> 00:19.187
That's when I realized
I had to change.

00:20.721 --> 00:23.391
So I made a list
of everything bad
I've ever done,

00:23.424 --> 00:26.360
and, one by one,
I'm gonna make up
for all my mistakes.

00:26.394 --> 00:28.329
I'm just tryin'
to be a better person.

00:28.362 --> 00:30.631
My name is Earl.

00:32.600 --> 00:36.604
* Come on, feet
Start movin' *

00:36.637 --> 00:38.506
* Got to get me there *

00:38.539 --> 00:41.475
[ Earl Narrating ]
Randy and I usually
avoid exercise at all costs,

00:41.509 --> 00:43.377
but sometimes there's
no way around it.

00:43.411 --> 00:45.413
[ Bird Shrieks ]

00:46.580 --> 00:48.482
[ Grunting ]

00:48.516 --> 00:51.485
[ Panting ]

00:51.519 --> 00:54.355
Can we take another break?
I'm having trouble...

00:54.388 --> 00:56.557
getting air into my mouth
and down to my stomach.

01:00.261 --> 01:02.563
[ Earl Narrating ]
Running out of gas
was karma telling me...

01:02.596 --> 01:05.299
it's time to do
number 62 on my list.

01:05.333 --> 01:07.501
A while back,
Randy and I came across...

01:07.535 --> 01:11.139
the only car
on the trailer park
without a locking gas cap.

01:11.172 --> 01:15.143
For about a month
before I won the lottery
and stopped stealing,

01:15.176 --> 01:18.279
that Yugo was like
our own personal Texaco.

01:20.681 --> 01:25.119
[ Earl Narrating ]
The first time we did it,
we used garbage bags.

01:25.153 --> 01:27.255
Oh!

01:27.288 --> 01:30.358
Then we found out gas
eats through garbage bags.

01:30.391 --> 01:32.560
Oh!

01:32.593 --> 01:35.596
Eventually, we learned
to put it in cans,
which we still had.

01:35.629 --> 01:38.499
So we filled 'em up
and headed over
to the trailer park...

01:38.532 --> 01:41.535
to return the gas
and cross it off the list.
Hey, Crab Man.

01:41.569 --> 01:43.904
Hey, Earl.
What you doin'?

01:43.937 --> 01:48.176
Just looking for
a car I stole gas from.
What's with all the magazines?

01:48.209 --> 01:51.445
Joy found my stash
of Classy Ass and she's
making me get rid of them.

01:51.479 --> 01:54.182
Man, that's a lot
of Classy Ass.

01:54.215 --> 01:56.217
I bet that's even more
than the president has.

01:57.485 --> 01:59.620
- Hey, dummy.
- [ Both ]
Hey.

01:59.653 --> 02:02.223
Darnell, I'm missin'
February '04
from this stack.

02:02.256 --> 02:04.325
You better not
be hidin' it.

02:04.358 --> 02:06.927
It's behind
the pretend fireplace.
I'll go get it.

02:06.960 --> 02:09.297
Darnell, I don't know
why you want to look...

02:09.330 --> 02:11.899
at that Miss February tramp
anyway when you got
all this right here.

02:11.932 --> 02:14.768
Darnell, you better look
at my boobs when I'm
talkin' about 'em.

02:16.404 --> 02:18.806
Let's go.
[ Whispering ]
Come on!

02:18.839 --> 02:21.209
[ Laughing ]

02:23.511 --> 02:25.413
[ Vacuum Whirring ]

02:37.891 --> 02:40.328
Excuse me.
Can I talk to you
for a second?

02:40.361 --> 02:42.863
I don't vote, I already
have a religion,
and I hate whales.

02:42.896 --> 02:45.299
No, no.
It's about your car.

02:45.333 --> 02:48.969
My name's Earl Hickey,
and I stole gas from you.
I never stole gas from you.

02:49.002 --> 02:51.505
No, I stole your gas.

02:51.539 --> 02:55.509
Look, I have a list--
Will you please
turn that thing off?

02:55.543 --> 02:58.412
[ Squeaking ]

02:58.446 --> 03:00.681
Give it to me.
Okay?

03:00.714 --> 03:02.483
[ Whirring Stops ]

03:02.516 --> 03:05.753
There. See? Nice.
Now we can talk.

03:05.786 --> 03:09.590
Hey! Hey!
Hey, what are you doing
with my garment pins?

03:09.623 --> 03:12.560
- Put my pins back!
- I wasn't gonna keep 'em.

03:12.593 --> 03:14.828
I'm just playin'
Daddy Long Fingers.

03:14.862 --> 03:17.765
Hey, calm down!
Put the-- Put the rock down!

03:17.798 --> 03:20.468
Look, see,
I have this list--

03:20.501 --> 03:23.671
And you want me
to sponsor you
by donating a dollar.

03:23.704 --> 03:26.540
What? No.
What I was gonna say is--
You need directions.

03:26.574 --> 03:29.310
I don't have time.
I have a list
of bad things I've done.

03:29.343 --> 03:32.012
That rug is very dirty
'cause it's gray.
I should've got the brown one.

03:32.045 --> 03:35.316
That's the color of dirt,
but I wasn't thinkin'.
I siphoned gas from you!

03:36.750 --> 03:40.754
When?
About this time
last year.

03:40.788 --> 03:43.991
But I'm bringin'
the gas back, see? Randy,
start unloading the gas.

03:45.793 --> 03:47.828
I did you wrong, but now
I'm makin' up for it.

03:49.830 --> 03:52.566
So, do you forgive me?
Can I cross you off
my list?

03:52.600 --> 03:54.502
Fine. Whatever.

03:54.535 --> 03:56.437
Thank you.

04:04.412 --> 04:08.582
[ Brakes Squeaking ]

04:08.616 --> 04:10.951
Man, that guy
was annoying, huh?

04:10.984 --> 04:14.021
Kinda like when you bite
the inside of your cheek,
and it swells up,

04:14.054 --> 04:16.824
and you keep bitin' it
and bitin' it and bitin' it.

04:16.857 --> 04:19.593
- Your cheek still
hurtin' you, Earl?
- Yeah, a little.

04:19.627 --> 04:22.696
Thanks for askin'.

04:22.730 --> 04:25.533
[ Horn Honks ]
[ Man ]
Get out of the road!

04:25.566 --> 04:28.502
- What the hell?
- [ Woman ]
Moron!

04:33.574 --> 04:36.444
What are you doin'?

04:36.477 --> 04:39.313
I'm gonna get hit by a car.
I'm killing myself.

04:39.347 --> 04:41.682
Is it because you're annoying?
I bet it's because
you're annoying.

04:41.715 --> 04:43.751
It's because if you hadn't
been stealing my gas,

04:43.784 --> 04:46.286
- I'd be dead already.
- What are you talkin' about?

04:47.721 --> 04:49.723
[ Earl Narrating ]
It ends up...

04:49.757 --> 04:52.092
the month Randy and I
kept stealin' gas...

04:52.125 --> 04:55.896
was the same month this guy
kept tryin' to kill himself
with car exhaust.

05:01.402 --> 05:03.637
[ Engine Stalls ]

05:06.374 --> 05:08.809
[ Earl Narrating ]
Only he never had
enough gas to do it.

05:15.849 --> 05:19.620
[ Engine Sputtering ]

05:19.653 --> 05:22.590
[ Earl Narrating ] Even though
he got close, the car always
died before he did.

05:22.623 --> 05:24.525
[ Engine Stalls ]

05:26.760 --> 05:28.662
Ah, nuts!

05:33.133 --> 05:35.869
[ Earl Narrating ]
After a couple weeks,
he finally gave up.

05:35.903 --> 05:39.339
Nuts! Nuts! Nuts!
Nuts! Nuts!

05:42.175 --> 05:45.012
Do you know how many times
I've vomited without getting
the benefit of dying?

05:45.045 --> 05:48.015
Seven? No, eight.
Forty-seven?

05:48.048 --> 05:51.585
[ Sputtering ]

05:51.619 --> 05:54.422
This entire time I think
that God is intervening
and saving me...

05:54.455 --> 05:57.691
for something real special,
but instead I'm just getting
screwed by a couple of thieves.

05:57.725 --> 06:00.528
Maybe God was saving you
to be screwed by thieves.

06:00.561 --> 06:03.096
And when there was only
one set of footsteps,

06:03.130 --> 06:06.534
maybe God was carrying you--
to be screwed by thieves.

06:06.567 --> 06:09.637
Randy. Can we just talk
about what you're doin'?
I mean, there's--

06:09.670 --> 06:12.039
A law against killing myself?
Yeah, I don't really care.

06:12.072 --> 06:15.042
What are they gonna do,
give me a ticket when I'm dead?

06:15.075 --> 06:17.845
There's a car coming.
You gotta move.
"No kidding, officer.

06:17.878 --> 06:19.980
- It's easy to remain
silent, cause I'm dead!"
- A car is coming!

06:23.751 --> 06:25.853
I'm killing myself,
and there's nothing
you can do to stop me.

06:27.621 --> 06:29.590
[ Car Approaches ]

06:35.863 --> 06:39.399
- Nuts!
- [ Horn Honking ]

06:40.634 --> 06:42.903
[ Honking Continues ]

06:44.572 --> 06:47.107
It's fine, Earl.
The carpet will protect him.

06:47.140 --> 06:49.877
Randy, I think we need
to help this guy.
I say we don't.

06:49.910 --> 06:52.513
You already crossed him
off your list.
I saw you do it.

06:52.546 --> 06:55.583
We don't have to help him.
We don't technically
have to help him.

06:55.616 --> 06:58.085
But we can't just walk away.
What are we supposed to do,

06:58.118 --> 07:00.454
- stand here and watch him
get run over?
- [ Horn Honks ]

07:00.488 --> 07:03.123
No, I don't want to see it.
But if we get in our car...

07:03.156 --> 07:05.626
and hear a thump and a scream,
that's none of our business.

07:05.659 --> 07:07.761
I'm sorry, Randy.
I can't explain it.

07:07.795 --> 07:10.564
This whole list thing
has me feelin' things
I've never felt before.

07:10.598 --> 07:13.567
I can't just walk away
from the guy.
Then let's run, Earl.

07:13.601 --> 07:15.869
Let's run away from him.
We could make it a race.
It'll be fun.

07:15.903 --> 07:19.006
Look, he's not that bad.

07:19.039 --> 07:22.843
[ Air Brakes Hiss ]
Hey, buddy,
today's your lucky day.

07:22.876 --> 07:25.045
I'm gonna help you find
a reason to live.

07:25.078 --> 07:27.981
[ Sneezes, Coughs ]

07:30.718 --> 07:34.888
You know, uh, most people
cover their mouths
when they do that.

07:39.593 --> 07:41.695
[ Earl Narrating ]
Findin' someone
a reason to live...

07:41.729 --> 07:45.699
isn't something I've ever
had to do before, especially
someone I hardly knew.

07:45.733 --> 07:47.968
So, suicide guy--

07:48.001 --> 07:50.638
Philo.

07:50.671 --> 07:53.674
Philo, uh, why do you
want to kill yourself?

07:53.707 --> 07:56.009
'Cause I don't have a job,
I don't have any friends,

07:56.043 --> 07:59.179
I live in a trailer
with no heat, I fail at
everything, and my feet hurt.

08:00.614 --> 08:02.550
You ever try
different shoes?

08:02.583 --> 08:04.484
I gotta go tinkle.

08:06.620 --> 08:11.191
"Tinkle." That is so stupid.
I wonder what he calls
goin' ploppies.

08:11.224 --> 08:14.962
Man, that guy is a drag.
Is he someone on your list?

08:14.995 --> 08:17.931
He was,
but I crossed him off,
so I'm finished with him.

08:17.965 --> 08:21.134
- But I'm helping him
anyway.
- Why?

08:21.168 --> 08:24.137
I don't know.
Guy wants to kill himself.
I can't just walk away from him.

08:24.171 --> 08:26.874
Are you gonna start helpin'
people that aren't
on your list now?

08:26.907 --> 08:29.877
'Cause if you do, we'll
never finish it and get
back to stealing again.

08:29.910 --> 08:32.279
You don't really understand
my list, do you, Randy?

08:32.312 --> 08:34.748
No. Not really.

08:34.782 --> 08:37.785
[ Metal Crashes ]
[ Rattling ]

08:38.952 --> 08:41.154
[ Water Dripping ]

08:44.892 --> 08:47.628
Oh, hi, guys.
Would either one of you
mind picking up...

08:47.661 --> 08:50.063
that broken pipe
and beating me
to death with it?

08:55.302 --> 08:57.671
- Randy, put it down.
- But, Earl, he said
he wanted me to--

08:57.705 --> 09:00.741
Put it down!

09:03.310 --> 09:06.647
[ Earl Narrating ]
I realized if I was gonna keep
Philo from killing himself,

09:06.680 --> 09:08.916
it wasn't enough
to just babysit him.

09:08.949 --> 09:12.586
I needed to find a way
to lift his spirits
and get him out of his funk.

09:12.620 --> 09:15.355
First I tried small talk.

09:15.388 --> 09:18.158
That's a real interesting
birthmark you got on the back
of your neck.

09:18.191 --> 09:21.094
My mom hit me with
a curling iron. I had spilled
cereal on the carpet.

09:21.128 --> 09:24.064
Didn't even have
milk in it.

09:24.097 --> 09:27.200
Hmm.
So your mom wears
her hair curly, huh?

09:33.040 --> 09:35.108
[ Earl Narrating ]
When small talk didn't work,

09:35.142 --> 09:38.679
we tried showin' him
other ways to have fun--
You know, like motel hockey.

09:48.656 --> 09:51.124
- Randy!
- That was a clean hit.

09:51.158 --> 09:54.662
[ Earl Narrating ]
Nothin' was workin', and since
suicide is a serious thing,

09:54.695 --> 09:56.897
I thought I should
consult an expert.

09:56.930 --> 09:59.066
Since experts write books,
I went to the bookstore,

09:59.099 --> 10:01.835
a place I had only been
once before.

10:01.869 --> 10:03.771
[ Man ]
Hey! Come back here!

10:07.174 --> 10:09.843
Excuse me, sir.
Uh, do you people have...

10:09.877 --> 10:13.781
anything here like a book
a guy can use to keep
a guy from killing himself?

10:13.814 --> 10:18.185
We have Self-Esteem For Dummies,
but I think that's sold out.

10:18.218 --> 10:20.821
Try the self-help section.

10:20.854 --> 10:23.056
Oh, and we also have
a large selection
of Books on Tape.

10:23.090 --> 10:25.358
What do you mean,
like, sticky?

10:25.392 --> 10:27.961
Cassette tape.
It's a book,

10:27.995 --> 10:30.430
but the author reads it
to you on tape.

10:30.463 --> 10:32.800
Book on tape.

10:32.833 --> 10:35.703
Wow. It doesn't get
any more futuristic
than that, huh?

10:35.736 --> 10:40.207
Well, actually it does.
You can download the books
directly to your iPod now.

10:40.240 --> 10:44.011
iPod, huh? What is that,
some sort of space capsule
or something?

10:47.447 --> 10:52.285
Think I got it.
It's a book on tape
called Something to Live For.

10:52.319 --> 10:55.388
I also got a novel version
of Road Hous read
by Patrick Swayze.

10:55.422 --> 10:57.691
The best cooler
in the business?

10:57.725 --> 11:00.393
This'll be great.
Books are written
by smart people,

11:00.427 --> 11:03.096
- and smart people know
how to fix problems.
- No, thanks.

11:03.130 --> 11:05.398
Come on, Philo.
I'm tryin' to save
your life.

11:06.934 --> 11:10.037
Catalina, hold up.

11:10.070 --> 11:13.040
I need to ask you a favor.
I got this guy who, uh--

11:13.073 --> 11:15.242
Well, he needs
something to live for.

11:15.275 --> 11:17.477
I am not sleeping
with that man.

11:17.510 --> 11:19.747
No, no.
Of course you're not.

11:19.780 --> 11:21.982
I know that.
Just make out
with him a little.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.984
No. I can smell him
from here.

11:24.017 --> 11:26.019
It's okay.
I'm not interested.

11:26.053 --> 11:29.823
I already got
a girl I love.
She's hot.

11:29.857 --> 11:34.327
- Wait. You love a girl?
- Yeah, but she hates me--
or she would if she met me.

11:34.361 --> 11:37.965
- I don't even know her name.
- Excuse me. I'm hot.

11:37.998 --> 11:40.901
You're okay, but compared
to my girl, you look like
one of those things...

11:40.934 --> 11:43.904
from The Lord of the Rings
that crawled out of the ground,
attacked the castle.

11:43.937 --> 11:47.007
This uniform is not flattering.
You should see me
in jeans and a bra.

11:47.040 --> 11:50.210
Ewoks.
Those are called Ewoks.

11:50.243 --> 11:53.480
Randy, this could be it.
If we can get this girl
Philo likes to like him,

11:53.513 --> 11:56.249
it'll give him something
to live for, and we won't
have to watch him...

11:56.283 --> 11:58.218
every second of every day.

12:01.321 --> 12:03.423
[ Water Bubbling ]

12:07.060 --> 12:09.229
[ Muffled ]
I'll get the hook.

12:09.262 --> 12:12.365
[ Earl Narrating ]
After we fished Philo
out of the bottom of the pool,

12:12.399 --> 12:18.205
we cleaned him up and got him
ready to go meet who we hoped
would be his new girlfriend.

12:18.238 --> 12:21.008
It finally felt like
I might actually get him
out of our lives,

12:21.041 --> 12:24.978
and I could go back to only
helping people on my list.

12:25.012 --> 12:27.881
That-- That's
the girl you love?
Yeah.

12:27.915 --> 12:31.118
Oh, please.
Victoria's Secret
is just as bad.

12:31.151 --> 12:34.087
Just 'cause they're classy
doesn't mean they're not
still whores!

12:36.056 --> 12:37.925
Son of a bitch.

12:43.030 --> 12:46.133
[ Joy ] I don't know why
you want a Prius when you
got a Maserati right here.

12:46.166 --> 12:48.902
[ Dog Barking In Distance ]

12:48.936 --> 12:51.238
You love Joy?

12:51.271 --> 12:55.242
Joy.
Classy name
for a classy lady.

12:55.275 --> 12:57.244
Sometimes I watch her
do laundry.

12:57.277 --> 12:59.212
So hot.

13:10.958 --> 13:14.127
[ Man ]
* The other day
I met a girl named Joy *

13:15.628 --> 13:22.335
* Oh, Joy to the world
was a beautiful girl *

13:22.369 --> 13:26.206
* But to me Joy meant
only sorrow **

13:26.239 --> 13:28.575
Look, you can't ask Joy
out on a date.
She's married.

13:28.608 --> 13:32.079
Oh, but she's always
yelling at her husband.
I know she's not happy.

13:32.112 --> 13:35.248
Well, that's her happy.
She's just a bitch.

13:35.282 --> 13:38.451
You know I love Darnell,
but if it'll get this guy
out of our lives,

13:38.485 --> 13:42.589
maybe we should consider,
you know, killin' Darnell.

13:42.622 --> 13:44.992
Randy, we're not
killin' Darnell.

13:45.025 --> 13:48.061
- I knew this wasn't gonna work.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa. No.

13:48.095 --> 13:51.498
H-Hold on now.
I-I think this could work.
Let me talk to Joy.

13:51.531 --> 13:53.934
Randy, take him back
to the motel.

13:53.967 --> 13:56.569
[ Exhales ]
All right, Philo,
would you rather--

13:56.603 --> 13:59.139
Sit in the back
of the truck
'cause you hate me.

13:59.172 --> 14:01.474
No, what I was
gonna say is--
That you hate me.

14:01.508 --> 14:04.077
I had to ride
in the trunk once.
It was raining--

14:04.111 --> 14:06.914
Pizza or burgers?
Pizza or burgers? Pizza!
Pizza! We're gettin' pizza!

14:06.947 --> 14:09.282
I like burgers.
Too bad.

14:09.316 --> 14:12.019
[ Earl Narrating ]
You may think me asking
my ex-wife for help was crazy,

14:12.052 --> 14:14.154
but sometimes you gotta
fight crazy with crazy.

14:14.187 --> 14:16.589
I wasn't flirting
with her, Joy.
She's a Girl Scout.

14:16.623 --> 14:19.960
I like Slim Mints.
Well, you ain't gettin' 'em,
'cause she ain't comin' back.

14:19.993 --> 14:23.163
Not after what I did
to her bicycle.

14:23.196 --> 14:27.901
Hey, Crab Man.
I was lookin' to have
a word with Joy.

14:27.935 --> 14:30.237
Hey, Earl. Come on in.
We're just fightin'.
Joy's jealous.

14:30.270 --> 14:32.539
I am not jealous.
You're the one that should
be jealous.

14:32.572 --> 14:35.308
I can't even walk
down the street without
guys offerin' to do me.

14:35.342 --> 14:37.978
I take that as a compliment.
I don't get jealous.

14:38.011 --> 14:41.014
That is a lie.
Everybody gets jealous.

14:41.048 --> 14:43.250
Hell, even frogs get jealous.
I saw that on TV.

14:43.283 --> 14:45.552
That's what all that
croaking's about.

14:45.585 --> 14:47.921
What do you want?

14:47.955 --> 14:50.123
[ Earl Narrating ]
I could tell it wasn't
the best time,

14:50.157 --> 14:53.093
but I asked Joy
my favor anyway.

14:53.126 --> 14:57.097
I figured if she'd sit down
with Philo and tell him
that she would date him...

14:57.130 --> 15:00.533
if she weren't already married,
it might give him enough
hope in the future...

15:00.567 --> 15:03.170
to stop tryin'
to kill himself.

15:03.203 --> 15:05.672
At least long enough
for me to walk away.

15:08.175 --> 15:11.178
Tell that little doofus
to meet me on Friday
at the Crab Shack.

15:11.211 --> 15:15.482
Really? Thanks, Joy.
This is a big help.

15:15.515 --> 15:18.551
Oh, and I hear you're
wearin' underwear again.
Good for you.

15:25.158 --> 15:28.595
Doesn't get jealous, huh?
[ Chuckles ]

15:28.628 --> 15:32.532
Boys, get Mama's
plastic stripper shoes
out of your Lego box.

15:32.565 --> 15:35.568
[ Earl Narrating ]
When the big day arrived,
I was feelin' nervous.

15:35.602 --> 15:38.305
It seemed like we were close
to finally gettin' rid of Philo,

15:38.338 --> 15:40.740
and I didn't want
anything to go wrong.

15:40.773 --> 15:44.077
Hey, Earl.
Hey, Crab Man.
Need a few beers.

15:44.111 --> 15:47.680
Oh, I'm sorry. Boss said
I can't serve you until you
fix that pipe in the bathroom.

15:47.714 --> 15:50.317
It sprays people
when they flush.

15:50.350 --> 15:53.453
Luckily, only a few people
that flushed so far.

16:08.768 --> 16:11.071
[ Exhaling ]

16:15.142 --> 16:18.611
You're breathin' loud.
That's because you made me
use toothpaste.

16:18.645 --> 16:21.081
It makes the sores
in my mouth sting.

16:35.495 --> 16:38.531
You that weird guy that likes
to watch me take my underwear
off my clothesline?

16:38.565 --> 16:40.700
- One of them.
Yes, ma'am.
- Beat it, Randy.

16:42.535 --> 16:44.337
[ Bell Dings ]

16:47.640 --> 16:51.711
I hear you have
a crush on me.
Yes.

16:51.744 --> 16:54.114
Hmm.
That's nice.

16:54.147 --> 16:56.183
Do me a favor?
Put your hand...

16:56.216 --> 16:59.119
on my leg right here
and just kind of
rub it around.

16:59.152 --> 17:02.222
Like that.
No, this side. Okay.

17:02.255 --> 17:04.757
You like that, darlin'?
Huh?

17:06.559 --> 17:08.661
'Cause I shaved
above the knee today.

17:10.730 --> 17:13.433
So much better
than a doll.
Hmm.

17:13.466 --> 17:16.669
[ Chuckles ]

17:16.703 --> 17:18.805
Get your hands
off my wife.

17:18.838 --> 17:21.208
What's the matter
with you?

17:21.241 --> 17:23.376
I thought you didn't
get jealous.

17:23.410 --> 17:27.814
Guess I was wrong. 'Cause
my heart feels like there's
blood gushing in and out of it.

17:27.847 --> 17:30.550
That's what a heart's
supposed to do.
Shut up!

17:30.583 --> 17:33.853
Oh, baby.
That's how my heart feels.

17:33.886 --> 17:36.123
That's all I needed
to hear.

17:41.828 --> 17:44.831
[ Chuckles ]
I'm so sorry.

17:44.864 --> 17:49.669
Uh-- Um, I thought
we were on a date.

17:49.702 --> 17:51.804
It was a date.

17:51.838 --> 17:53.873
But not all dates
are good ones, honey.

17:53.906 --> 17:57.477
Sometimes it ends up
with your sweetie doin'
a black man in the bathroom.

17:57.510 --> 17:59.412
Come on.

18:05.885 --> 18:08.288
What are you doin' here?
Where's Philo?

18:08.321 --> 18:12.425
- He's gone. I blew him off.
- Damn it, Joy.
I told you he's suicidal.

18:12.459 --> 18:14.361
Come on, Randy.

18:22.802 --> 18:25.638
[ Earl Narrating ]
I wanted to find Philo
as fast as I could,

18:25.672 --> 18:27.707
but we had to stop for gas.

18:27.740 --> 18:30.810
It made sense.
I'd stolen gas
more than once.

18:30.843 --> 18:33.680
Karma was payin' me back
more than once.
[ Bird Shrieks ]

18:33.713 --> 18:37.250
We gotta stop, Earl.
I can feel my heartbeat
in my teeth.

18:37.284 --> 18:40.420
Sorry, Randy. We can't.
We gotta get
to a gas station.

18:40.453 --> 18:42.489
I'm not lettin' Philo
die on my watch.

18:48.661 --> 18:51.464
[ Earl Narrating ]
And then I saw the thing
I feared the most.

19:00.607 --> 19:03.776
- Hi, Earl.
- Holy Moses!

19:03.810 --> 19:06.813
You scared
the crap out of me.
I thought you were dead.

19:06.846 --> 19:09.949
Dead? [ Laughs ]
Why would I be dead?
You crack me up, Earl.

19:09.982 --> 19:12.552
I was just listening
to this tape you gave me.

19:12.585 --> 19:15.555
- I don't have a cassette
player in the house.
- I thought you killed yourself.

19:15.588 --> 19:17.724
Kill--
[ Man ] Doesn't that give you
something to live for?

19:17.757 --> 19:20.327
Why would I kill myself?
That's crazy.

19:20.360 --> 19:22.629
Is it? The woman you love
just blew you off,

19:22.662 --> 19:25.765
and two days ago you tried
to kill yourself 'cause
a squirrel looked at you wrong.

19:25.798 --> 19:29.302
I know.
But that was before
I had friends.

19:29.336 --> 19:31.604
Excuse me?

19:31.638 --> 19:34.607
Yeah. I mean there's
no reason to kill myself
now that I got friends.

19:36.609 --> 19:40.280
If he has friends,
how come they haven't been
helping instead of us?

19:40.313 --> 19:43.616
I think he means us,
Randy.

19:43.650 --> 19:45.685
[ Earl Narrating ]
That's when I realized...

19:45.718 --> 19:48.588
that while Randy and I
were tryin' to find him
a reason to live,

19:48.621 --> 19:51.858
he found it on his own--
us, his new friends.

19:51.891 --> 19:55.328
Hey, why don't you guys come in
and watch my old wrestling tapes
from high school?

19:55.362 --> 19:59.532
I wasn't on the team or nothin',
but me and my sister
had some real close matches.

19:59.566 --> 20:02.902
I know you don't
understand why, Randy,
but I gotta go inside.

20:02.935 --> 20:05.672
If you want
to take the car--
I'll go in there with you.

20:05.705 --> 20:08.408
Really?
Yeah. That guy didn't kill
himself 'cause of us, Earl,

20:08.441 --> 20:10.610
and that's kinda cool.

20:10.643 --> 20:14.547
Makes me feel weird
in my stomach, but I like it.
Is that why you wanna help him,

20:14.581 --> 20:17.484
'cause of that weird feeling
in your stomach?
I guess it is.

20:17.517 --> 20:19.619
Hey, come on.
I cleaned all the junk
off the couch.

20:19.652 --> 20:22.822
I found a real big blanket
we can sit under.

20:22.855 --> 20:25.925
How long you think
we need to be his friends?

20:25.958 --> 20:28.628
I'm not sure.
I still
don't like him, Earl.

20:28.661 --> 20:32.031
I know, Randy.
I don't like him either.

20:32.064 --> 20:34.367
* I'm happy at home

20:34.401 --> 20:35.735
* Happy at home

20:35.768 --> 20:38.571
* You're my best friend *
